
                                            Ngoepe - who's only the second African-born player in Major League Baseball - is in Cape Town this week with community organisation Play Sport4Life.

                                         CAPE TOWN - South African pro baseball player Gift Ngoepe says he has big plans when he heads back to the United States next year. Ngoepe - who's only the second African-born player in Major League Baseball - is in Cape Town this week with community organisation Play Sport4Life. The 27-year old has been in several areas sharing his story and baseball tips with young players from disadvantaged communities. Ngoepe, who was traded from the Pittsburgh Pirates to the Toronto Blue Jays, says he's excited to start spring training next year. “I’m excited about this new venture and I think it’s a great move. I’m excited to go back to training.” 